The paper deals with the complexity of queries with logical formulas in a setting where the underlying structure or database changes over time. This falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also explores the applicability of methods for parameterised algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses case studies for various well-known parameterised problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
